12:
Oh, huh, you're right… Hmm, it might
be coming from that store over
there?
15:
Hello there, would you happen to be
customers?
18:
I am Harlisha.
Would you perhaps like to come
inside my clinic for a moment's rest?
21:
Erm, we're not really sick or injured
or anything at the moment, so…
25:
Hehe, worry not, my clinic accepts
even the healthy! The medicine we
practice is ...slightly different from
what you might be used to!
27:
According to our teachings, the
seed of disease is thought to be
borne of stress, exhaustion, and
stagnation.
29:
And so, the path to healing lies in
rest, relaxation, and … well, just
feeling good!
31:
That's a novel approach if I've ever
heard one!
33:
Hehe, well if you wish to know more,
why not stop by and have a rest?
37:
Well, now I'm intrigued, so … why not!
Plus, taking a short break couldn't
hurt.
42:
Excellent, excellent! In that case,
please come this wa—Oww.
46:
Ahh, I'm terribly sorry!
I'm… I'm such a klutz sometimes…
50: Well, anyway, please come this way!
57: Ahh, that's a really pleasant aroma.
61:
If you feel drowsy, don't hesitate to
lie down and have a nap, like miss
Stella is doing, hehe.
65: Hmm, I might just… go and do that.
73:
Oh, I'm so sorry for yelling like that!
It's just... I seem to have run out of
the herbs I need to perform my
treatments.
74:
I'll head to the nearby ruins to pick
some more. Please stay here and
rest while I do so!
82:
Nothing to worry about, just leave it
to me--- oof.
88:
That's hardly a sight that inspires
confidence.
97:
Alk? Is that you? Why did you come
all the way here?
100:
I just didn't feel right leaving you all
alone.
104:
I see... It seems that you were the
one most in need of my treatment
after all!
107:
Well, thanks for coming along, hehe.
I'm really fine though, I promise. See?
112:
The incense you burned... put them
to sleep?
115:
That's right. Even monsters need to
rest sometimes!
119:
Shall we head inside while they're
still napping?
125: Hehe, well, how do you feel?
128:
Good morning.
Incredible, I feel completely
refreshed.
135:
Unfortunately there wasn't time for
me to perform the full treatment on
you, Alk.
139:
You don't have to worry about me.
I'm used to this kind of work.
142:
You're all travelers, right?
Please—allow me to accompany
you on your journey.
145:
That way I could properly finish off
Alk's treatment!
148:
I really appreciate the sentiment,
but what about your clinic?
151:
Actually, the contract for this clinic…
expires today! So that's no problem.
154:
I usually travel around by myself,
looking for people to help with my
healing arts.
158:
Where are you planning to head
next?
161:
Rather than the destination, I prefer
to focus on the journey. It's an
important part of my training to
become an even better healer.
165:
Well, I think Starview Village will be
an excellent place to continue your
journey.
170:
A place where many people
congregate. It will no doubt be
helpful for your training. And what's
more is…
172: I greatly approve of your treatment.
175: Hehe, I'm very glad to hear that!
